commit.message:
REF: Remove "ForwardRef" in evaluated annotations

When the stringified object is not available for literal
replacement, `ForwardRef('...')` is used, but by that time
we already need the whole annotation, so just unwrap it.

Longer-term should maybe switch away from
using `inspect.formatannotation()`.

commit.message:
BUG: Fix circular imports when fetching type annotations

Don't set `typing.TYPE_CHECKING` as it can result in circular imports.
See https://github.com/pdoc3/pdoc/issues/245#issuecomment-682180052

Instead, fallback to raw annotation strings when other,
eval'ing methods fail.

Ref: https://github.com/pdoc3/pdoc/issues/245

commit.message:
ENH: Offline search with lunr.js (#209)

* Offline search with lunr.js

* Fix mr requested changes:
 - Proper naming
 - Fixed some bugs
 - Separate search.mako and html.mako
 - Remove `--html-search-type`
 - Changed hard to read code and simplified it
 - Added some explanation comments

* More MR feedback
- Removed useless CSS that was left by mistake
- Added some lines removed by mistake
- Undo some code moving
- Remove a unused parameter
- Remove magic numbers
- Remove documentIndex and modified index in index.js to fit the use
- Added some explanation comments
- Change lunr_search config to take in a dict and in there any further config

* Forgot to fix tests

* Forgot to remove this

* Allowed settings empty dict for default lunr_search config

* Revert unrelated change

* Reword config.mako

* Move variable closer to where it's used

* CSS fixups

* Use *minified* CDN resource

* Fixup HTML template

* Make search index a normalized, minimal list, with docs id'd by position

* lunr: boost name more than refname

* Refactor pdoc.cli; print generated paths for search index

* Trim index docstrings somewhat

* Merge matchData for the same result, listing each refname at most once

* Add form element label for a11y

* search.mako: move <footer> and <scripts> inside <body>

* Apply search fuzziness to every query term

* Show search results in a modal dialog on the same page

* Search via URL fragment (hash) to avoid webserver cache misses

* Fix bugs
  - Replace `dobj.refname` with `dobj.name`
  - Allow correctly setting `lurn_search` to `{}`

* Fix more bugs
  - Fix XSS vulnerablity
  - Remove `~` from the search result string

* More bugfixes and improvements
  - Revert setting `ref` to `name`
  - Generate index for classes
  - Add a missing `;`
  - Fix boosts

* Added ability to disable indexing docstrings

* Fix incorrect url indexing

* Fix comments from pr
  - Fix field boosts
  - Reformat code

* Optimized index loading

* Added missing `;`

* Fix lurn config

* Use mako comments which are stripped at compile time

* Show verbose query

* Don't strip newlines from index

This actually _saves_ almost 1KB while also making
versioning/debugging the file much easier.

* Rename config option lunr_search.docstrings → .index_docstrings

* Reformat back. Nested functions and closures are fine.

* Reword config

* Simplify. We already know about generated files via Module.submodules()

* Minor JS lint

* Fix mypy/typing

Co-authored-by: Kernc <kerncece@gmail.com>

commit.message:
BUG: Better handle raw URLs and markdown links (#203)

* Display link text correctly

In generated documentation the link text placed into [] is not followed
by left angle brakcet and it redirects to the given website. Moreover,
improved regular expression enables displaying url given in parentheses
or url containing them, i.e.:

(https://example.com)
https://example.com/more_(examples)

* match code span fences or arbitrary length

* some touch-ups
